# Negative Constraints

## DOM Access
- NEVER use `document.getElementById()` — use React refs
- NEVER use `document.querySelector()` for component state — use Jotai atoms or AppState
- NEVER directly manipulate DOM for canvas — use the renderer pipeline

## Components
- DO NOT suggest class components — only functional components with hooks
- DO NOT use `React.FC` — use plain function declarations with typed props
- DO NOT create HOCs — use hooks or composition patterns

## Types
- DO NOT use `any` type — always provide proper types
- DO NOT use `@ts-ignore` or `@ts-expect-error` without explanation
- DO NOT create new type files — extend existing ones in `types.ts` or `packages/element/src/types.ts`

## State
- DO NOT use `useState` for app-level state — use `actionManager` or Jotai atoms
- DO NOT use `useReducer` for complex state — use the action system
- DO NOT mutate arrays/objects in state — always create new references

## Tests
- DO NOT modify test snapshots manually — regenerate with `yarn test -u`
- DO NOT mock canvas API unless absolutely necessary
- DO NOT skip tests with `.skip` without a TODO comment

## Dependencies
- DO NOT add Redux, MobX, Zustand, or any state management library
- DO NOT add react-konva, fabric.js, pixi.js, or any canvas abstraction
- DO NOT add lodash — use native JS or existing utils

## Custom Libraries
### @excalidraw/math — REAL API:
- `pointRotateRads(point, center, angle)` → Point
- `pointRotateDegs(point, center, angle)` → Point
- `pointDistance(p1, p2)` → number

### @excalidraw/math — DOES NOT EXIST (AI may hallucinate):
- `rotatePoint()` — use `pointRotateRads` or `pointRotateDegs` instead
- `normalizeRadians()` — not in this lib
- `Math.rotate()` — not a method
- `calculateAngle()` — not in this lib
- `vectorLength()` — use `pointDistance` instead

## How to verify
- Grep for `document.getElementById` in new code — should find zero
- Grep for `class.*extends.*Component` in new code — should find zero
- Grep for `: any` in new code — should find zero (except justified cases)
- No new state management library imports
